 \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Test contract frozen before code: authoritative contract is the ticket AC plus the existing scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py bare invocation. Preconditions: a stateful fake subprocess receives exactly [jscpd,--reporters,json,--output,<temp>,<scan-root>] and writes a production-shaped jscpd-report.json; absence injects FileNotFoundError at that subprocess seam. Production path: shared _jscpd.run_jscpd consumed by public jscpd_dup.analyze and the existing backfill clone reader. Tier: in-process unit/contract tests with a stateful verified CLI fake because the external jscpd binary is irreducible and absent from gating CI; a live known-clone canary is supplementary/skip-if-absent. Observable postconditions: exact clones/percentage, AnalyzerResult.duplication, exact Unavailable reason/accruing_since, and unchanged backfill clone count. Negative controls: nonzero/missing report must not become zero metrics. Collateral invariant: backfill uses the same bare command contract and retains its int clone_count shape. Recovery/statefulness: read-only temp report, no recovery contract.","timestamp":1784849773237500001},{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Held-out validation complete. Standard-tier implementer produced the implementation in one substantive attempt; two subsequent reapplications were only required by revert-first oracle corrections (overall dispatch count 3). Final oracle: 8 passed, 1 supplementary live-jscpd skip. Adapter and backfill expose the same shared run_jscpd callable, missing/nonzero executions yield Unavailable rather than zeros, and legacy backfill tests remain green. Defect-seeded mutation changed parsed clones from report value to zero; the happy contract failed on exact clones and passed after restoration. Refactoring litmus: assertions use command/result behavior; the sole structural identity assertion is explicitly required by the ticket reuse-import AC.","timestamp":1784850287532590001}],"created_at":1784517470005593001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"efc2fb66-9990-4ca9-8e66-433b5d5533d2","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"9597-1b85-d2ab-4eed"},{"link_uuid":"c8187884-ec25-4c4a-9c34-5598baf5cb43","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb"},{"link_uuid":"e7d8f9cf-0280-4f5b-a0fb-a28aac4a88b6","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"3b30-2168-ba16-41fc"}],"description":"## Description\nDuplication analyzer running jscpd (external PATH CLI, JSON reporter) -> `AnalyzerResult.duplication` (clone count + duplicated-lines %). No LLM/prompt/schema/enum is defined by this ticket (T8 not-applicable — this is a deterministic CLI adapter, no agent/reviewer/output-schema surface).\n\n## Grounding (E4/G1G2 — verified via Grep/Read)\n- CONFIRMED `grep -n \"jscpd\\\\|statistics\" scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py`: the existing `_measure_clone_count` shells the BARE binary `[\"jscpd\", ...]` and reads `statistics.total.clones` from the JSON report.\n- New files CREATED here: `analyzers/jscpd_dup.py`, `analyzers/_jscpd.py`. `AnalyzerResult`/`Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` from 3b30 (depends_on). Consumer updated OUTSIDE dir: the backfill script (re-pointed at the shared helper; invocation byte-for-byte unchanged = still bare `jscpd`).\n\n## Approach & rationale (G6/T1)\nExtract the backfill jscpd runner + `statistics.total` read into `analyzers/_jscpd.run_jscpd`; both the backfill script and the new adapter call it. Rationale: one runner = no invocation drift; reuses a mature OSS CLI already integrated (no novel architecture, T1). Invocation stays BARE `jscpd` (npx explicitly out of scope) so the backfills behavior is unchanged. `accruing_since` is a module-level `_ACCRUING_SINCE` constant (matching existing reader modules), passed to `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command)\n- [ ] `run_jscpd` in `analyzers/_jscpd.py` parses `statistics.total.clones` (int) + `statistics.total.percentage` (float). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_jscpd_dup.py::test_parse_statistics_total`.\n- [ ] Backfill + adapter share ONE runner. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_jscpd_dup.py::test_single_runner_reused` (asserts both modules reference `_jscpd.run_jscpd`).\n- [ ] jscpd present: `analyze(root)` on a known-clone fixture returns `.duplication.clones >= 1`. PROVE (skipif jscpd absent): `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_jscpd_dup.py::test_live_clone -m integration`.\n- [ ] jscpd ABSENT (monkeypatched runner raising FileNotFoundError): returns `Unavailable(reason, _ACCRUING_SINCE)`, not zeros, not a raise. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_jscpd_dup.py::test_absent_jscpd_unavailable`.\n- [ ] Backfill invocation unchanged (still bare `jscpd`). PROVE: `grep -q \"\\\\[.\\\\?.jscpd\" scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py` (no `npx` introduced).\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 9597, e7a0 (recorded depends_on edges).\n## Files: src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/jscpd_dup.py (new), src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_jscpd.py (new), scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py (delegate), tests/unit/metrics/test_jscpd_dup.py (new)\n## Scope: M","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/jscpd_dup.py","reason":"new duplication adapter (bare jscpd)"},{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_jscpd.py","reason":"new shared jscpd runner extracted from backfill"},{"path":"scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py","reason":"point at shared helper; invocation unchanged (bare jscpd)"},{"path":"tests/unit/metrics/test_jscpd_dup.py","reason":"new: import-assertion proof of reuse + monkeypatched runner"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","3b30-2168-ba16-41fc"],["depends_on","9597-1b85-d2ab-4eed"],["depends_on","e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb"],["parent","839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051"]],"parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","parent_status_uuid":"76e86815-5009-4978-9edd-c80ad4c4dda5","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_id":"3ba0-9350-8337-429a","ticket_type":"story","title":"Duplication analyzer adapter via jscpd (clone detection, deterministic shell-out)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["5e755b0f-9dc1-4b03-8545-f0fce1da7451","efc2fb66-9990-4ca9-8e66-433b5d5533d2","c8187884-ec25-4c4a-9c34-5598baf5cb43","1b604b95-1eb3-4d2d-9504-2053d3755a55","83f72cae-8933-4f23-be2d-1fb145d2786e","4739a3ee-d937-45bc-ada9-008bfd02701d","e7d8f9cf-0280-4f5b-a0fb-a28aac4a88b6","231b44c1-9b3c-4b57-9381-285f9e97da4a","61b042e7-a7ac-4f47-9c13-c2a54ab1a5a9","8cf9dad8-e748-4ec7-a2a8-e590c3b44aef","110e2d94-d23e-4457-886e-b17e86dfd7d2","76e86815-5009-4978-9edd-c80ad4c4dda5","4bd97e6c-00a9-402f-9076-1c6e2b0f38c7","c3d4ecf0-ca42-4c99-9819-b84c8879aadb","74cdab4b-1e9f-4376-a1bb-a3bd6e63acf0"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784850287532590002,"uuid":"7f0de7a8-118f-4d4e-8127-9c90ef1ae89d"}